","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England","Liskeard, Cornwall, England":"Liskeard, Cornwall, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Agnes","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized version of the Greek name <i>Hagnē</i>, from the feminine form of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705193,"age":5,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705195,"age":50,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Agnes Carnother was born in 1332, in Cornwall, England, her father, Walter Carnother, was 46 and her mother, Mrs Walter Carnother, was 47. She married Richard Upton about 1355. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1399, in her hometown, at the age of 67."},"et":{"1332–1399":"1332–1399","1331–1398":"1331–1398","1356–1450":"1356–1450","1286–Male":"1286–Surnud","1286–Female":"1286–Surnud","1286":"1286","1450":"1450","1382":"1382","1337":"1337","1356":"1356","1399":"1399","1332":"1332","1398":"1398","1453":"1453","ABT 1355":"umbes 1355","1331":"1331","about 1356":"umbes 1356","about 1332":"umbes 1332","Upton, Cornwall, England":"Upton, Cornwall, England","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England","Liskeard, Cornwall, England":"Liskeard, Cornwall, England"},"fi":{"1332–1399":"1332–1399","1331–1398":"1331–1398","1356–1450":"1356–1450","1286–Male":"1286–Kuollut","1286–Female":"1286–Kuollut","1286":"1286","1450":"1450","1382":"1382","1337":"1337","1356":"1356","1399":"1399","1332":"1332","1398":"1398","1453":"1453","ABT 1355":"noin 1355","1331":"1331","about 1356":"noin 1356","about 1332":"noin 1332","Upton, Cornwall, England":"Upton, Cornwall, England","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England","Liskeard, Cornwall, England":"Liskeard, Cornwall, England"},"fr":{"1332–1399":"1332–1399","1331–1398":"1331–1398","1356–1450":"1356–1450","1286–Male":"1286–Décédé","1286–Female":"1286–Décédée","1286":"1286","1450":"1450","1382":"1382","1337":"1337","1356":"1356","1399":"1399","1332":"1332","1398":"1398","1453":"1453","ABT 1355":"environ 1355","1331":"1331","about 1356":"environ 1356","about 1332":"environ 1332","Upton, Cornwall, England":"Upton, Cornouailles, Angleterre","Cornwall, England":"Cornouailles, Angleterre","Liskeard, Cornwall, England":"Liskeard, Cornouailles, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Agnes Carnother est née en 1332, à Cornouailles, Angleterre, son père, Walter Carnother, avait 46 ans et sa mère, Mrs Walter Carnother, avait 47 ans. Elle a épousé Richard Upton environ 1355. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Elle est décédée en 1399, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 67 ans."},"de":{"1332–1399":"1332–1399","1331–1398":"1331–1398","1356–1450":"1356–1450","1286–Male":"1286–Verstorben","1286–Female":"128